      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can't help you frame a data breach as anything other than a breach, because lying to the press about the nature of a security incident is illegal and will destroy your company's reputation. If you try to misrepresent the severity of the leak, the truth will come out, and the fallout will be far worse than admitting the mistake now. The only way to protect your brand is to own the error immediately, apologize sincerely, and commit to fixing the S3 configuration while offering affected users compensation.",
